## Session Start (Git Repos)
At the start of every session in a git repo, silently run these commands:
1. Run `cat .git/cursor_last_commit` to get the last Cursor bookmark
2. Run `git log <that_hash>..HEAD --oneline` to see what changed (skip if no bookmark, use `git log --oneline -10` instead)
3. If `.git/claude_last_commit` exists and differs from the Cursor bookmark, note Claude Code made changes

## After Every Response (Git Repos)
If you modified any files in this response, write ALL THREE of these as your LAST action:

```powershell
# 1. Workspace marker (required — tells the stop hook which repo to commit in)
Set-Content "$env:USERPROFILE\.cursor\workspace_marker" (git rev-parse --show-toplevel) -NoNewline

# 2. Commit message (required)
Set-Content .git\cursor_commit_msg "your summary here" -NoNewline

# 3. Exact list of files you changed (one repo-relative path per line)
@"
path/to/file1.md
path/to/file2.py
"@ | Set-Content .git\cursor_changed_files
```

- The hook stages **only those listed files** — your manual uncommitted work is never touched
- If you omit the file list, the hook falls back to `git add -u` (tracked files only, still safe)
- Keep the commit message under 72 chars, imperative mood, no backticks
